All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy) — stops before the last index
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — processes all elements including the last
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The condition `i < items.length - 1` caused the loop to exit one iteration early, so the last element was never pushed into `results`. Removing `- 1` fixes the off-by-one error, and all 6 tests (4 for `processItems` + 2 for `sum`) now pass.

